<TITLE> Six firms vie for Bibiyana power plant </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 8 (bdnews24.com)  Six companies Thursday submitted pre-qualifications bid documents for the 450MW Bibiyana Power Plant expected to be on stream by 2011 at the latest, Md Abdul Jalil, director general of the Power Cell, told bdnews24.com. Korea Electric Power Corporation (South Korea), AES Corporation (USA), a consortium of Powertek Berhad (Malaysia), Siemens Project Ventures Gmbh(Germany), Chevron Corporation (USA), YTL Power International Berhad (Malaysia) and a consortium of Summit Industrial & Mercantile Corporation and GE Energy LLC (USA) submitted the proposals, the power ministry said in a statement. The independent power plant (IPP) project will be implemented on a build-own-operate basis. The government will have a 22-year power purchase agreement with the selected company. An evaluation committee headed by the director general of the Power Cell under the power division will evaluate the bidding documents. Pre-qualified bidders will be announced within two weeks, said the statement. The companies meeting the pre-qualifications criteria will enter the final round of bidding, expected to take place in the second quarter of 2008. The Power Cell has also invited private concerns to submit pre-qualifications bid documents for another IPP in Sirajganj. The deadline for application for the Sirajganj plant ends on Dec 11. bdnews
